   In his new post, Starr will be the federal government's chief
representative before the Supreme Court. tarr, 42, was a clerk for
former Chief Justice Warren E. Burger and later a partner with the
Los Angeles law firm of Gibson, Dunn &amp; Crutcher. He served as
counselor to then-Attorney General William French Smith from 1981
until he was appointed to the D.C. Appeals Court in 1983.
