<HEAD>Kassebaum Wants a Third Term</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. Nancy Kassebaum has changed her mind and
decided to seek a third term in the Senate.
   When the Kansas Republican was first elected, she promised that
she would only serve two terms.
   She said Thursday she changed her mind and will run again next
year. She was bothered by breaking her pledge, she said.
   However, she argued that it would hurt Kansas if she limited her
tenure when others in Congress are not subject to similar
restrictions. There is no limit on the number of terms a person can
serve in the Senate or the House.
