<HEAD>Thunderstorms Drench South, Midwest</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 6th graf, `Twisters in ...' to CORRECT that homes were
destroyed in East Feliciana Parish, sted East Baton Rouge.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms lingered in much of the South and
Midwest today, and rescuers in New Jersey used an Army vehicle
designed for fording rivers in wartime to evacuate residents from
flooded areas.
   Heavier rainfall during the 6 hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included more than 5 inches at Fort Myers, Fla., nearly 2 inches at
Biloxi, Miss., and 1} inches at Baton Rouge, La.
