   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms extending
from the central and eastern Gulf Coast across much of the
Mississippi and Ohio valleys into the upper Great Lakes; showers
and some thunderstorms across the northern Rockies and the northern
Plains; snow showers in parts of Montana; and rain showers across
northwest Washington state.
   Predicted highs: 40s in parts of Montana; 50s and 60s in the
northern Pacific Coast and the eastern slopes of the northern and
central Rockies; 90s in the desert Southwest and the western third
of Texas; and 70s or 80s across much of the rest of the nation.
