<HEAD>Fires Rage Through Four Villages, Killing 20</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire swept through four villages in
southern Andhra Pradesh state, killing 20 people, injuring 50 and
destroying more than 500 houses, news reports said Friday.
   The cause of the Thursday blaze in the villages of Luthunuru,
Kamparaopet, Sirikonda and Madhunuru was not known, officials told
the United News of India.
   Relief operations were under way in the remote region Friday
night, the news agency said, but provided no details.
   Grain and property worth an estimated $1.25 million were
destroyed in the blaze, according to the Press Trust of India news
agency.
   The villages are about 650 miles south of New Delhi.
