<DOCNO> AP890519-0110 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-05-19-89 1418EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d a AM-BRF-HospitalKilling     05-19 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF-Hospital Killing,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Suspected Bellevue Killer-Rapist Changes to Insanity Plea</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Note contents.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homeless man accused of raping and murdering a
pregnant doctor at a hospital in January changed his plea Friday to
innocent by reason of insanity.
   Steven Smith, 23, had pleaded innocent to an indictment charging
him with the murder of Dr. Kathryn Hinnant in her Bellevue Hospital
office-laboratory late Jan. 7.
   ``We now admit he committed the crime,'' said Smith's lawyer,
Marvyn Kornberg. ``But we say he did not know what he was doing
because he did not have the mental capacity to form the intent to
commit the crime.''
   Smith, arrested Jan. 9 at a men's shelter, originally had said
he helped an accomplice named John strangle the 33-year-old woman
while robbing her. He claimed it was John alone who raped her.
   Kornberg said lab tests show that semen and some of the blood at
the scene came from Smith. The lawyer said this shows there was no
``John'' and therefore Smith is delusional.
   State Supreme Court Justice James Leff scheduled hearings for
June 21.
