<HEAD>North Korea Says it Will Pay Special Bonus to Workers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   North Korea said Friday it will pay a bonus to all
workers, technicians and office employees in June before the 13th
World Festival of Youth and Students opens in Pyongyang in July.
   The bonus of 100 percent of regular monthly wages would be paid
under a decree adopted Thursday by the Central People's Committee,
according to official Korean Central News Agency, monitored in
Tokyo.
   The bonus will be paid ``in appreciation of the feats performed
by the working class and other laboring people in the past 200-day
campaigns,'' the report said.
   The youth festival with an anti-imperialist theme will be held
in the North Korean capital July 1-8. Officials say 30,000 people
from more than 170 countries are expected for the festival, a major
political, cultural and sports event involving mostly communist and
Third World nations.
