<HEAD>Drought Helped Improve Wheat Quality</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Last year's drought may have reduced wheat
production but it apparently helped improve overall quality of the
grain, the Agriculture Department said Friday.
   A report by the department's grain inspection service said 57
percent of the samples of wheat from the 1988 crop were graded U.S.
No. 1, up from 49 percent in 1987. The agency said the average
moisture content of 1988 wheat also was lower than in 1987, while
the protein content of the grain was up.
