<SECOND>AM-Sweden-Terrorists,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Suspects Held Over In Bomb Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men of Arab origin were arraigned
on Friday on charges of complicity in four terrorist bombings in
Scandinavia and Holland.
   Swedish Television said the men were linked to the Syrian-based
Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine-General Command. An
official statement said the two were about 35 years old, but did
not identify them by name.
   An announcement by Chief Prosecutor Stefan Karlmark said police
were questioning the two in relation to two bomb attacks in
Denmark, one in Sweden and one in Amsterdam in 1985-86.
   The bombing of a Northwest Orient Airline office in Copenhagen
in May 1985 killed one person, the statement said.
   The two were among 15 people rounded up by security police
Thursday. A police statement said 10 were released after
questioning and three others were held over in robbery
investigations.
   The PFLP-GC organization is a major supect in the bombing of Pan
American Flight 103 over Scotland last December, which killed 270
people. The police statement made no reference to that attack.
