<FIRST>r a AM-Obit-Adderley     05-19 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Adderley,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Patriarch of Musical Clan is Dead at 85</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Funeral services are scheduled Monday
for Julian C. Adderley, patriarch of one of the nation's most
influential musical families.
   Adderley, who died in a hospital Wednesday at the age of 85, was
the father of jazz trumpeter Nate Adderley and saxophone great
Julian ``Cannonball'' Adderley, who died in 1975.
   Adderley's grandson, Nathaniel, is a musician who has worked
with Aretha Franklin and Luther Vandross.
   The elderly Adderley played with professional jazz groups after
graduating with a degree in education from Florida A&amp;M. He was an
English teacher and guidance counselor at Leon High School for many
years.
   Adderley, a native of Key West, was preceded in death by his
wife Jessie Lee.
</TEXT>
