<FIRST>r f PM-Midway-FirstClass     05-19 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Midway-First Class,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Midway Adds First Class Service To Flights</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Midway Airlines plans to introduce first-class
service to all flights beginning this fall.
   The move from all-coach seating is in reponse to the popularity
of upgrading to first class among frequent fliers, said Chairman
David R. Hinson.
   Midway also announced a tentative marketing agreement with Air
New Zealand to coordinate flight connections of the two carriers
through Los Angeles Airport. Hinson said he wants to make two or
three more agreements with Asian carriers, and is interested in
discussions with European carriers.
   ``We want to globalize Midway,'' Hinson said.
   Since Midway announced an agreement with Canadian Airlines
International, the Chicago-based carrier has seen a substantial
increase in passengers making connections at Chicago's Midway
Airport from Canada, Hinson said.
</TEXT>
